{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4f17e982-2a2d-42be-8b9b-c23f6506dc38","content":"\n\nNeither — use **`dotnet watch`**.\n\n- `dotnet watch test` — re-runs tests automatically when files change.\n- `dotnet watch run` — restarts/hot-reloads an app on changes.\n\nSince your project appears to be a test project, you'd want:\n\n```\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` execute once and exit — they don't monitor for file changes, so hot reload doesn't apply to them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"596c9050-2313-427c-bfe5-ea6d1ac06187","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about hot reload in .NET - specifically whether to use `dotnet test` or `dotnet run` to benefit from hot reload. Let me look at their project to understand the context.","outputTokens":170},"id":"60dacb36-11e8-47bc-96b8-e812f485e377","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:46:28.876Z","parentId":"f3a33553-556e-41c7-81cc-e41745cbae85"}
